1
00:00:03,534 --> 00:00:06,354
Being good with AI doesn't mean using it for everything.

2
00:00:06,634 --> 00:00:08,084
 It means knowing how to use it well.

3
00:00:09,304 --> 00:00:11,104
 Here's what that looks like in practice.

4
00:00:11,614 --> 00:00:15,214
 A marketing manager uses AI to draft three different angles for a 

5
00:00:15,254 --> 00:00:18,704
campaign pitch, then picks the strongest one and rewrites it in her 

6
00:00:18,754 --> 00:00:19,224
voice.

7
00:00:19,844 --> 00:00:23,374
 A consultant asks AI to summarize a hundred pages of industry 

8
00:00:23,444 --> 00:00:26,744
reports, then spends an hour verifying the key claims before 

9
00:00:26,764 --> 00:00:28,054
putting them in front of a client.

10
00:00:29,014 --> 00:00:34,124
 A project lead uses AI to stress-test a project timeline, asking "what 

11
00:00:34,154 --> 00:00:36,914
could go wrong with this plan?" before presenting it to 

12
00:00:36,954 --> 00:00:37,854
