13
00:00:38,664 --> 00:00:41,244
 None of these people are handing their work over to AI.

14
00:00:41,644 --> 00:00:44,834
 They're using it to think faster, explore more options, and catch 

15
00:00:44,884 --> 00:00:48,344
things they might miss. Then they apply their own judgment.

16
00:00:48,664 --> 00:00:50,094
 Here's why this matters.

17
00:00:50,334 --> 00:00:52,904
 In a professional setting, you own what you submit.

18
00:00:53,224 --> 00:00:56,584
 If a client asks you to explain a finding in your report and you can't 

19
00:00:56,644 --> 00:01:00,124
because AI generated it and you never really understood it, that's a 

20
00:01:00,154 --> 00:01:03,954
problem. Not a policy problem. A credibility problem.

21
00:01:04,394 --> 00:01:06,434
 The skills on this page will help you avoid that.

22
00:01:07,094 --> 00:01:10,504
 You'll learn how to prompt AI so it gives you something useful, and 

